The Cohomological Gauge Theory 

We will now describe a remarkable cohomological symmetry of the
partition function (), with path integration measure
(), which will be the crux of much of our ensuing
analysis of the quantum gauge theory. For this, we linearize the Yang-Mills
action in the field strength  via a functional Gaussian integral
transformation defined by an auxilliary field  as
Z= ^-g^2 2^2  A  
