irreducible Schrodinger representation of the constant curvature
condition, and  is the  representation of the
Weyl-'t Hooft algebra in two dimensions. The latter algebra is known
to possess a unique irreducible unitary representation of dimension
, , so that module decomposes into irreducible
components as
_p,q =L^2()(W __1 W __N )  ,
where  are the irreducible
representations of the Weyl-'t Hooft algebra and
